FBIS4-34872 "drlat123_b_94007" FBIS-LAT-94-123 Daily Report 24 Jun 1994 Dominican Republic Haiti Ministry Note: Pro-Aristide Acts `Null and Void' Ministry Note: Pro-Aristide Acts `Null and Void' FL2406230194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1500 GMT 24 Jun 94 FL2406230194 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole French BFN [Text] The Foreign Affairs and Cults Ministry has ordered former President Jean-Bertrand Aritide and his employees not to speak on behalf of the Haitian state or to commit the Republic of Haiti to anything with their signatures. This is how it appears in the Ministry press release, which adds: The Haitian Chancery expresses its most formal reservations over statements and actions by members of the overthrown government, statements and actions that the Chancery considers null and void. The Foreign Affairs and Cults Ministry adds that it has asked the OAS secretary general to pass this information on to its various members and regional institutions for whatever it's worth.
